 Her Majesty The Queen. It is with your encouragement, particularly over the last few years, that we feel prepared to make this adjustment.</p><p class="mol-para-with-font">'We now plan to balance our time between the United Kingdom and North America, continuing to honour our duty to The Queen, the Commonwealth, and our patronages.Â </p><p class="mol-para-with-font">Â 'This geographic balance will enable us to raise our son with an appreciation for the royal tradition into which he was born, while also providing our family with the space to focus on the next chapter, including the launch of our new charitable entity.</p><p class="mol-para-with-font">'We look forward to sharing the full details of this exciting next step in due course, as we continue to collaborate with Her Majesty The Queen, The Prince of Wales, The Duke of Cambridge and all relevant parties. Until then, please accept our deepest thanks for your continued support.'Â </p></div></div><p class="mol-para-with-font">Back then, the daughter of Queen Victoria's third son was expected to marry royalty and had once been tipped as a future Tsarina of Russia.Â </p><p class="mol-para-with-font">Instead, she chose to marry a (very posh) commoner, Alexander Ramsay, at Westminster Abbey.Â </p><p class="mol-para-with-font">In doing so, she readily agreed to surrender her royal styles and titles on her wedding day, though not her place in the line of succession.Â </p><p class="mol-para-with-font">She was given the title of 'Lady Patricia' for the rest of her life.Â </p><p class="mol-para-with-font">As such, she is the only member of the family who has entered a church as a Princess and left as 'Lady'.</p><p class="mol-para-with-font">I doubt it is a template which will appeal to the Duke and Duchess of Sussex.Â </p><p class="mol-para-with-font">But that is the clearest example of someone offloading the 'senior' royal status which Harry and Meghan wish to shelve.</p><p class="mol-para-with-font">How pointless all that talk of a 'slimmed-down Royal Family' looks now.Â </p><p class="mol-para-with-font">With three 'senior' members of the family now out of the frame â the Duke of York very much against his wishes and the Sussexes by their own design â that crucial but unsung day-to-day work of regional visits and generally representing the Monarch will now land on fewer shoulders.</p><p class="mol-para-with-font">The Queen will now be more grateful than ever for the oft-neglected input of the Princess Royal, the Wessexes and the cousins, royalty who seldom flourish in the spotlight but who now, more than ever, will be needed to help to keep the show on the road.</p><p class="mol-para-with-font">That show will go on, of course, because it always has and because this is an institution that has always been far stronger than any individual.Â </p><div class="mol-img-group xwArtSplitter" style="style"> <div class="mol-img"> <div class="image-wrap"> <img id="i-49fc1ca7b2abc64a" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2020/02/13/09/23129916-7866007-The_10million_property_where_Meghan_and_Harry_spent_six_weeks_ov-a-7_1581587578066.jpg" height="648" width="962" alt="The Â£10million property where Meghan and Harry spent six weeks over Christmas and New Year" class="blkBorder img-share" style="max-width:100%" /> </div> <noscript> <img id="i-49fc1ca7b2abc64a" src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2020/02/13/09/23129916-7866007-The_10million_property_where_Meghan_and_Harry_spent_six_weeks_ov-a-7_1581587578066.jpg" height="648" width="962" alt="The Â£10million property where Meghan and Harry spent six weeks over Christmas and New Year" class="blkBorder img-share" /> </noscript> </div> <div><div> <span></span> <div></div></div></div><p class="imageCaption">The Â£10million property where Meghan and Harry spent six weeks over Christmas and New Year</p></div><div><div data-track-module="am-related_carousel^related_car