"mol-style-bold">The Duke, 35, and <a style="font-weight: bold;" href="/tvshowbiz/meghan-markle/index.html" id="mol-92efab31-327e-11ea-93c2-e98aacf49af2">Duchess of Sussex</a>, 38, who made their first ever appearance together at the Invictus Games in Toronto on 25 September 2017, have squeezed in endless memorable moments in the time that has followed.Â </span><span class="mol-style-bold">Â </span></p><p class="mol-para-with-font"><span class="mol-style-bold">Among their jam-packed schedule includes their official engagement announcement in November 2017, and the multi-cultural and US-influenced wedding that followed at Windsor Castle, on May 2018.</span></p><p class="mol-para-with-font"><span class="mol-style-bold">The star-studded day was filled with VIP guests and dominated by Hollywood stars including the Clooneys, the Beckhams, Idris Elba, <a style="font-weight: bold;" href="/tvshowbiz/oprah-winfrey/index.html" id="mol-92efd240-327e-11ea-93c2-e98aacf49af2">Oprah Winfrey</a>, Tom Hardy and James <span class="mol-style-bold">Corden.Â </span></span>Â </p><p class="mol-para-with-font"><span class="mol-style-bold">Other highlights since their big day include Meghan's lavish baby shower trip to New York, which is thought to have cost more than $500,000 (Â£380,000), Archie's birth on 6 May 2019, and their 10-day tour of Africa as a family late last year.Â </span></p><p class="mol-para-with-font"><span class="mol-style-bold">Here, FEMAIL looks back at the Duke and Duchess' engagements since the first moment they stepped into the public eye together.Â </span><br /></p><div class="mol-img-group xwArtSplitter" style="style"> <div class="mol-img"> <div class="image-wrap"> <img id="i-f90cbe95779af6a7" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-src="https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2020/02/13/09/23161576-7866007-Prince_Harry_and_Meghan_Markle_watched_Wheelchair_Tennis_at_the_-a-13_1581587578104.jpg" height="730" width="962" alt="Pr